NASA Presidential Campaign Committee chairman and ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi has urged voters in Western to vote for candidates in his party.His remarks in Kakamega county are likely to heighten internal competition within NASA, where each of the five co-principals is bidding for their candidates.Mudavadi said NASA flagbearer Raila Odinga (ODM), Wiper&rsquo;s Kalonzo Musyoka, Moses Wetang&rsquo;ula (Ford Kenya) and Isaac Rutto of CCM are pushing for the election of their candidates and he will do the same.&ldquo;I want you to give me more seats and that way you&rsquo;ll be strengthening me in the NASA tent for future bargaining,&rdquo; Mudavadi told a rally at Matioli market in Lurambi constituency on Sunday. Mudavadi received outgoing Lurambi MP Raphael Otaalo, who defected from ODM to ANC at the rally. Otaalo will be part of the NASA presidential campaign.